## History / Discovered In

This rule was originally extracted from production findings in the LeadScraper project, where a structured audit identified seven concrete duplication patterns spanning storage adapters, dependency wiring, runtime configuration, domain-model instantiation, and external-service configuration. The detailed historical catalogue — sprint references, file paths, and consolidation strategies per finding — is preserved in **ADR-005** in this repository.

For consumer projects, the relevant signal is the **decision flow** above (Distinguishing Real Duplicates from Polymorphism): every code review should walk the four-question checklist before consolidating or duplicating an implementation.
